```cpp // Bootstrap: initialize control-plane connections between all ranks auto bootstrap = std::make_shared<mscclpp::TcpBootstrap>(rank, world_size); // Create a communicator for connection setup mscclpp::Communicator comm(bootstrap); // Setup connections here using comm ... // Construct the default proxy mscclpp::ProxyService proxyService(); // Start the proxy proxyService.startProxy(); // Run the user application, i.e., launch GPU kernels here ... // Stop the proxy after the application is finished proxyService.stopProxy(); Whilethedefaultimplementationalreadyenablesanykindsofcommunication,MSCCL++alsosupportsuserstoeasilyimplementtheirowncustomizedproxiesforfurtheroptimization.Forexample,thefollowingexamplere-defineshowtointerprettriggersfromGPUs.

